cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces an epistemic extension of Strategy Logic with imperfect information and solves the model-checking problem on a class of hierarchical instances. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper deals with reasoning about knowledge and strategies, which are important topics in AI. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses strategic reasoning and distributed synthesis. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with solving a problem on a class of hierarchical instances. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses a solution to a class of strategic problems with epistemic temporal specifications on hierarchical systems, which could be relevant to software engineering.
